## Common questions

- Do I need a referral? No — you can book directly, including for ACC claims.
- Is it covered by ACC? Yes, when treatment is for an accident-related injury (osteopathy and acupuncture). We can lodge the claim for you at your first visit.
- Is osteopathy safe during pregnancy? Yes — gentle techniques are used and are safe across all trimesters.
- Can osteopaths treat babies and children? Yes, using gentle non-invasive techniques adapted for younger patients.
- Is acupuncture painful? The needles are finer than a hair; most patients feel deeply relaxed during treatment.
- Can acupuncture help with fertility or IVF? Yes — it can complement both natural conception and assisted reproductive treatments.
- Are Chinese herbs safe with other medications? Usually yes, but tell your practitioner about every medication and supplement so they can prescribe safely.

